prime, the derivatives.

00:04:26.050 --> 00:04:30.970
It just happens that when we
plug it in, the c1 and the c2

00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:36.630
themselves disappear because
these were null solutions.

00:04:36.630 --> 00:04:40.570
So we know that c1
constant would be good,

00:04:40.570 --> 00:04:45.480
but when we put it in
there, we get equations that

00:04:45.480 --> 00:04:48.160
involve c1 prime at each time.

00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:49.650
So I'll take that away.

00:04:49.650 --> 00:04:51.000
At each time.

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:51.650
All right.

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:55.020
Two equations, two
unknowns, we solved it.

00:04:55.020 --> 00:04:57.150
OK.

00:04:57.150 --> 00:05:01.920
And then when we solve them,
we put them back in to y of t

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:04.310
